commitResults.messageTitle: Implement the Sort Command for People
commitResults.messageBody:
Following additions of two new classes:
* SortCommand.java
* SortCommandParser.java

And changes made to existing classes to support the sorting of people,

* We are now able to sort the lists of people displayed by the
lexicographical order of their names (e.g. Amanda would appear higher
up in the person list as compared to Ben after sorting because the
letter A appears earlier than B following alphabetical orders.

Renamed source as sources to reflect its nature as a list.
Merge updated parser classes.

Added parent classes ArticleCommand and PersonCommand with commandType()
method for future use in switching UI view between articles and persons upon command execution.

between saving of person or article to json.

Renamed mentions of source to sources to reflect list nature of the
variable.

Renamed source prefix in commands form `src/` to `O/` to reflect
intended future change to naming the variable as "Outlets".

Minor bug fix for AddArticleCommand incorrectly applying the tag prefix
instead of source prefix.

Added ArticleListPanel and ArticleListCard classes and fxml to handle
displaying of articles on the UI.

Modified MainWindow class and fxml to include ArticleListPanel.

Fixed EditArticleCommand incorrectly checking isAnyNonNull() to correctly accept edits to single or
multiple attributes.

Fixed incorrectly interpreting `<cmd> -a` commands without a trailing
whitespace as commands pertaining to persons.

Allowed for multiple authors and sources to be added during the editing
command.
